# 11) Security Requirements

## Authentication

* Secure admin login
* Password hashing with Argon2 or bcrypt
* Session-based auth or JWT with refresh strategy
* HttpOnly cookies for tokens

## Authorization

* Role-based access control
* Permission checks on every protected route
* Middleware route guards for admin

## JWT strategy

Recommended:

* Short-lived access token
* Refresh token in secure cookie
* Token rotation on refresh
* Server-side revocation support if needed

## Input validation

* Zod schemas for every form and API route
* Sanitize all rich text and file inputs
* Prevent SQL injection through ORM
* File type and size validation

## Rate limiting

* Contact/inquiry endpoint limits
* Login attempt throttling
* File upload rate control
* IP-based abuse protection

## Environment variable handling

* Keep secrets server-side only
* Validate env on boot
* Separate dev/staging/prod env files
* Never expose DB or auth secrets to client bundles

